In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. proclaims March 2023 as American Red Cross Month. He highlights the importance of the American Red Cross and their commitment to providing compassion and care in times of disaster and crisis. The Red Cross offers assistance in the form of food, shelter, and emergency supplies during hurricanes, wildfires, tornadoes, and other emergencies. They also respond to crises overseas and help with disaster preparedness. President Biden encourages Americans to donate blood, learn first aid, and participate in events to prevent home fires. He urges citizens to support the work of service and relief organizations and honors the Red Cross for their dedication to making the world a better place.